        <b><font size="-1" color="#000000">PREPARATION:</font></b><font color="#000000"><br>
        Lemon Grass is best prepared in a teapot or covered steeping cup using 
        1-2 teaspoons of herb per serving. Before infusion, moisten the leaves 
        with a few drops of hot water to release the sweet lemon scent. Then fill 
        the pot with boiling water and allow to steep 2-3 minutes. Lemon Grass 
        may be resteeped several times by gradually increasing the infusion time.</font></p>
